modules.description: Processes elements of a map incrementally, applying a function only to newly added keys. Works with `Map.t` from the parameter module, tracking dependencies and updating results as the input map changes. Useful for efficiently handling dynamic sets of data where each element requires independent computation, like monitoring file system changes or user session tracking.

This module implements incremental computations that automatically update when dependencies change, using changeable values and computations tracked through `t` and `cc` types. It supports operations like `read`, `map`, and `write` to build dynamic data flows, and `var`, `change`, and `propagate` to interface with external state. Concrete use cases include efficiently tracking and transforming live data streams, such as monitoring dynamic file sets or maintaining reactive UI elements.
